  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The food at the Hotel Portavesco is varied and plentiful.</p>
<p>The breakfast buffet has plenty of hot and cold choices.</p>
<p>For dinner you'll enjoy a four-course meal including antipasti, a buffet of vegetables and delicious mains.</p>
<p>Special dinners on Christmas Day and New Year's Eve are included.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">If you're looking for a hotel with easy access to the slopes, the Hotel Portavescovo is perfect. You are close to the village centre and the ski lifts, plus at the end of the day you can ski back to the hotels ski room. When you return you can make the most of the small wellness area and a delicious evening meal.</span></p>
<h2><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Great location</span></h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">With a great location at the foot of the piste, getting onto the <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites Ski Area</a> couldn't be easier. The nearest lift is the Burz chairlift, head up here to access some of the lovely slopes around Passo Campolongo, and access to the Alta Badia region.  If you are after some more challenging runs, make your way over to the Porta Vescovo area, or for some of the best views in the area, the Marmolada is easily accessible from Arabba.</span></p>
<h2>Restaurant &amp; Bar</h2>
<p>The hotels cosy restaurant is a lovely spot to start and end the day. Fuel up for the day at the varied breakfast buffet before hitting the slopes. For dinner, the restaurant serves both regional and classic Italian cuisine. Once a week you can sample some of the tasty dishes of the region at the Ladin buffet and on Fridays a fish dinner is served.  Join your family and friends in the hotel bar, and plan your itinerary for the following day over a drink or two. The Stube bar has an upbeat atmosphere and serves a good selection of drinks.</p>
<h2>Relaxation</h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">After a day of exploring the Sella Ronda, take a moment to relax in the wellness area with a small swimming pool, steam-bath and sauna. For the more active, there is a fitness room with a range of equipment. For the ultimate treat</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> book yourself in for a massage after a long day on the mountain.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
